        <mxCell id="Ejs32dkQ2-U0xZNUx5ii-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;How it works (Auth)&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. The Frontend Application comprises of a very simple Flask server that renders some UIs for the user to be able to view the satte of the infrastructure and to perform actions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;2. The USER Will need to log in to access the UI&lt;br&gt;3. The UI Server performs actions on the backend through an API CLIENT, which authenticates with the access key that is present in the env vars of the frontend server.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="340" x="290" y="760" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
